<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-08T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-08T07:00:00-05:00" n="648" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d648">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">858.248/10–844: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-08T13:00:00+01:00">October 8,
                                    1944—1 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 1:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>8487. We have given Foreign Office orally the substance of Department’s
                            8247, October 7, 7 p.m.<note n="81" xml:id="d648fn1">See footnote 80,
                                    <ref target="#pg_697">p. 697</ref>.</note> When doing so we were
                            told that a message had just been received from the British Minister at
                            Stockholm stating that the Secretary General of the Swedish Foreign
                            Office had informed him that Madame Kollontay already knows of the
                            proposed release of airmen and had been promised that in any release
                            effected 10 Russian internees would be simultaneously released “on
                            account”.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Stockholm and Moscow.</p>
                        <p>Our 8372, October 5, 7 p.m. has also been repeated to Moscow and
                            Stockholm.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>